name: Land Of The Forlorn, World #00
description:
|"A random thought flashed through my mind tonight, a question for you to be exact; have you ever felt like you are willing to pay somebody to kill you? An investment in getting disappeared, the superimposition of a will to be gone and the lack of guts regarding even your truest suicidal thoughts. Feeling overqualified whenever you try to achieve happiness in life is the biggest hindrance you would ever create for yourself, the whole conception is a big lie to be honest and oh god the whole contrast is just hilarious don't you think?"- Written on the very last page of the journal. – Your perception of the statement; "The life you live is not the life you deserve.", has a lot to do with how you get up each morning and move on with your life, it represents itself in each and every single act you do during the day, and here I am "…Slipping away at the end of the day into dreams of the two of us running away…".   |
